+The recommended launch sequence prioritizes market credibility and engineering learning:
 
-These include:
+Phase 1 — Sidekick Air (therapy market — establishes product category)
+Phase 2 — Sidekick Sport (athletic market — extends reach and visibility)
+Phase 3 — Sidekick Rescue or Sidekick Medical (institutional markets — platform credibility)
+Phase 4 — Sidekick Recovery (consumer market — volume opportunity)
 
-mobile therapy professionals  
-sports medicine and recovery environments  
-emergency and rescue operations  
-field medicine and remote healthcare  
-consumer recovery and wellness markets  
+Each phase should build on the engineering, manufacturing, and market lessons of the prior phase.
 
-By building multiple products on a shared structural platform, StitchCore can expand across these markets efficiently.
